obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47327)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165&sectionId=47327&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the International`
  line `Development Association (Status, Immunities and Privileges) Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 15th October, 1960,`
  line `vide notification No. S.O. 2474A, dated 11th October, 1960, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47328)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165&sectionId=47328&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Agreement" means the Agreement for the establishment and operation of the international`
  line `body known as the International Development Association;`
  line
  line `(b) "Association" means the International Development Association established under the`
  line Agreement.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (47329)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Conferment of status and certain immunities and privileges on the Association and conferment of certain immunities and privileges on its officers and employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165&sectionId=47329&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in any other law, the provisions of Article VIII of the Agreement set`
  line `out in the Schedule shall have the force of law in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in section 9 thereof shall be construed as--`
  line
  line `(a) entitling the Association to import into India goods free of any duty of customs without any`
  line `restriction on their subsequent sale therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) conferring on the Association any exemption from duties or taxes which form part of the price`
  line `of goods sold; or`
  line
  line `(c) conferring on the Association any exemption from duties or taxes which are in fact no more`
  line `than charges for services rendered.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend`
  line `the Schedule in conformity with any amendments, duly made and adopted, of the provisions of the`
  line `Agreement set out therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (47330)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165&sectionId=47330&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (47331)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Notifications under section 3 and rules under section 4 to be placed before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165&sectionId=47331&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00005_196032_1517807319165
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under sub-section (2) of section 3 and every rule made under`
  line `section 4 shall be laid as soon as may be after it is issued or made before each House of Parliament while`
  line `it is in session for a period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or ^1in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree for making any modification in the notification, or as`
  line `the case may be, in the rule, or both Houses agree that the notification or rule should not be issued or`
  line `made, the notification or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as`
  line `the case may be, so however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that notification or rule.`
